<Response>None< /Response>< text>
Delicious food.  My favorites are the pumpkin curry and sauteed eggplant/tofu.  I sometimes get takeout (only because I live close by) and am usually surprised at how few people are here, because the food is great, the atmosphere quiet, and the decor pleasant .  The only disappointment for me (ever) has been the brown rice, which isn't quite what I'm used to.  It's seldom busy, but don't let that deter you!  Glad to give this great little place a thumbs up.< /text>

< user_name>
Fire flower</user_name>
<GmapID>0x80dcdd4b5a07308d:0xaebc89837e4ed218<//GmapID>< Review>
I'm reviewing this place after taking numerous trips to this location. After the countless visits to this store I can honestly say that this location has the WORST customer service and without a doubt is DISCRIMINATORY towards people of color like myself.
Let me start by saying that I'm a Rouge member, which means that I spend more than the average consumer. The service that I've received has been less than stellar, especially from management. There have been times where I've been straight up ignored or not even acknowledged. Other times where I politely ask for something, and a cast member will instead show me a different product from the one I had asked about. I've also been ignored when I ask for help, and instead a cast member will go to someone else who is wearing an expensive handbag. Other times I get followed around the store, because they think I might be stealing. I'll get stared at from across the store. Its an uncomfortable feeling, and it makes me feel awful everytime it happens.
I believed at first that maybe it was just me. So, I changed my appearance. I dressed up in expensive clothes, fixed my hair for a couple of my trips, and dressed up humbly for other trips. I was treated with respect and kindness when I dressed nicely. Sales associates flocked to help me. They saw the jewelry/handbag I was wearing and probably thought I was finally worthy of their time.

When I walked into this store wearing workout clothes, I was followed around the store. I was watched with a close eye, because they thought I was going to steal. Sales associates insisted that I use a basket to carry my items when all I was carrying was a small lipstick, and sephora concealer. I couldn't swatch anything without someone keeping a close eye on me. When I went to checkout the cast member didn't acknowledge that I was a Rouge member even after scanning my phone. She immediately assumed that I wasn't a member at all and was charging me full price, knowing that their was ae
Rouge sale. I asked her about when that sale started. She looked at me as if this information wouldn't matter to me, and she feigned to forget when it was. I asked about the VIB sale and somehow she could magically remember those dates instantly. I told her I was a Rouge member and had to show her my Sephora app to prove that I wasn't lying to get my discount. She rolled her eyes, and finally gave me my discount.
I think I'm done with this store location. I hate being treated like I'm a criminal. I hate feeling like I'm not worthy of help. I'm done with this location, and will take my business to Ulta from now on.<//Review>

<Rate>3< /Rate>< Text>
I like this Sephora since it's only about 5 minutes from my place. Otherwise, for high end brands like SK-II and other selections, I prefer going to the South Coast Plaza location off of Bristol st. The South Coast Plaza location also has better makeup artists and a larger selection of gift sets. This Sephora is smaller but has the basic essentials. I also get the occasional makeover here as well. Weekends get packed so schedule a makeover in advance!

Since this location is smaller, it is usually less busy. Last weekend for the VIB rouge 20% off sale, I got most of my items at the South Coast Plaza Sephora. Then I came to this tustin location with my husband to get some last minute items. I like to go to both locations as the selections are different. As for makeup classes, this location does not have any as of yet, so I recommend going to the South Coast Plaza location instead. Overall, a decent store for last minute items and sometimes has what I'm looking for.< /Text>

<userid>104391725146946372378< /userid><username>Julie Healon<//username><Date>1503118095720<//Date><Rate>5</Rate>< review>
Super nice! The lady gave us a bunch of free donuts, and holes. It's 9:30 PM. I'm guessing get rid of em before they close. That's the best time to go.

Donuts are good. Even though they are from this morning. They still taste pretty fresh. Lots of selections.

Typical donut shop. Rows of donuts, some muffins. Cinnamon rolls. Lot's of teas. And coffee. Also bottled beverages. It looked like they had some croissants as well.

We tried to call again to apologize and try to explain the situation and we see if there was anything we could do to make it work which unfortunately was unresolved.\nWe always try and send 30-1hr notice before we arrive. If no answers we leave a message/Text and wait up to 30min then try again and again if no answer we leave message that we couldn‚Äôt get an approval that someone would be home and if Service was still needed please call back so we could come and provide service. We then proceed to the next stop and still keep job on the route until we get a call that we would be able to access Home for service.\nThanks for the feed back and we will look into our process and see where we can improve service for each and every customer.'}<//response><gmap_id>0x8090512a59430f29:0x447f1bc6bcd18e14< /gmap_id></record></dataset><record>

< text>
This is a great place to start a bike ride.  There are roads on either side of U.S. 395 that extend north and south of here for at least 20 miles.  The east side has a road behind the Pleasant Valley dam that is closed to cars for around five miles.  The road surface is poor, but it's quite scenic with high rock walls on either side.  You can do a loop from here that runs about 28 miles.< /text>

This was the North Palm Springs, CA location. It was not bad food wise, but the rest was questionable! The restaurant itself is clean for as busy as it is. Staff is patient and kind. But the environment and outdoors of the property does not feel safe at night at all! They NEED security. Badly.  Too much traffic and the parking is not well lit at all. I kept being approached by pan handlers and worse type people and nothing is done about it! Scary. And I am a tough woman, but still kind and do not mind helping those in need if it is legit. It was especially busy with brazen drug dealers and sex traffickers/workers prevailent in the area. Those people were not good people and kept approaching everyone, outside arriving to ise any of tje facilities there, but I will spare those details. It really made me angry and I call 911 to report it before I left after my meal, I was concerned for other innocent people, especially those with small children or woman by themselves. I do recommend carrying mace or other defense if your a woman using this location at night! And be very, very wary of your surroundings and please never walk alone!! Ever. Regarding the food... I am Vegetarian for medical reasons, so their full menu does not have many items that cater to those with diet restrictions or health preferences to choose from. It was late or I would have found somewhere else that did. So I went with their sour cream and chive baked potato with extra cheese sauce on the side. It was good. The menu is a little too pricey though, for fast food in my opinion! But the food is always good when it is made correctly. Security not so good. It is connected to a Pilot gas station a Cinnabon.  Be careful y'all. At night at least. I was literally approached by a male escort), a man selling illicit drugs, and a man asking for money. To which I kindly donated my last $1 to that I had on hand. I am a good, honest person. Not trying to create drama. I am just truly concerned for the welfare of the travelers and consumers who use this Wendy's/Pilot Station rest stop. I would hate tk see anyone get hurt just because they stopped to have a nice fast food meal. I'd give 5 stars but cannot due to my experience on their joint property outdoors.
